<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-1576] Brazilian Analyzer doesn&apos;t remove stopwords when uppercase is given</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1576</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;The order of filters matter here, just need to apply lowercase token filter before removing stopwords&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;	result = new StopFilter( result, stoptable );&lt;br/&gt;
		result = new BrazilianStemFilter( result, excltable );&lt;br/&gt;
		// Convert to lowercase after stemming!&lt;br/&gt;
		result = new LowerCaseFilter( result );&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Lowercase must come before BrazilianStemFilter&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At the end of day I&apos;ll attach a patch, it&apos;s straightforward&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;not applicable&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
